'''Brian Myers''' (born April 15, 1985) better known by his ring name '''Curt Hawkins''', is an [[United States|American]] [[professional wrestling|professional wrestler]]. He is currently signed to the [[World Wrestling Entertainment]] (WWE) working on its [[WWE SmackDown|SmackDown]] brand. Upon making his debut in the WWE Hawkins formed a tag team with [[Zack Ryder]] where they would go on to capture the [[WWE Tag Team Championship]].

==Professional wrestling career==
===World Wrestling Entertainment (2006<U+2013>present)===
====Tag team career (2006-2009)====
{{main|Curt Hawkins and Zack Ryder}}
=====Developmental territories (2006<U+2013>2007)=====
On February 24, 2006, Brian Myers signed a developmental contracts with [[World Wrestling Entertainment]].<ref name="OWW">{{cite web|title=Major Brothers at Online World of Wrestling|url=http://www.onlineworldofwrestling.com/profiles/m/major-brothers.html|accessdate=2007-06-16}}</ref> He was given the [[ring name]] Brian Majors and teamed up with [[Zack Ryder|Matthew Cardona]] who was given the ring name Brett Majors, to form the [[tag team]] the [[Curt Hawkins and Zack Ryder|Majors Brothers]]. Together they won the [[Deep South Wrestling]] [[DSW Tag Team Championship]] on two occasions. They later won the [[OVW Southern Tag Team Championship]] once.<ref name="Gerweck">{{cite web|last=Gerweck|first=Steve|title=OVW Six Flags Super Summer Sizzler Series #3 Results|url=http://www.gerweck.net/news/1181965768.shtml|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20070621154646/http://www.gerweck.net/news/1181965768.shtml|archivedate=2007-06-21|date=2007-06-15|accessdate=2007-06-16}}</ref>

=====The Major Brothers (2007)=====
The team was moved from the developmental league to the main roster, changing their last names from "Majors" to "Major". The team worked on WWE's [[ECW on Syfy|ECW]] brand. The team won their first match but since then failed to win any matches in ECW, in either singles or tag team competition<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wwe.com/shows/ecw/archive/06052007/|title=Chairman falling deeper and deeper into the abyss|date=2007-06-05|author=Bryan Robinson|accessdate=2007-11-11|publisher=WWE}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wwe.com/shows/ecw/archive/05082007/|title=Spirit of ECW Splashed|date=2007-05-08|author=Bryan Robinson|accessdate=2007-11-11|publisher=WWE}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.wwe.com/shows/ecw/archive/05222007/|title=Experiencing painful revenge|date=2007-05-22|first=Bryan|last=Robinson| accessdate=2007-11-11|publisher=WWE}}</ref> They moved from ECW to [[WWE Friday Night SmackDown|SmackDown!]] on June 17, 2007, as the eighth pick in the [[WWE Brand Extension#Supplemental Draft|2007 Supplemental Draft]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wwe.com/shows/smackdown/archive/06152007/articles/sddraftreport|title=SmackDown drafts up|accessdate=2007-11-11|publisher=WWE}}</ref> On Smackdown the team had only slightly more success than on the ECW brand, defeating the team of [[Chavo Guerrero, Jr.|Chavo Guerrero]] and [[Jamie Noble]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wwe.com/shows/smackdown/archive/07132007/|title=Officially on|accessdate= 2007-11-11|publisher=WWE}}</ref> On November 9, 2007, they received a tag title match after winning a number one contender's battle royal, but could not defeat the champions, [[Montel Vontavious Porter]] and [[Matt Hardy]].<ref name="Finding the way">{{cite web|url=http://www.wwe.com/shows/smackdown/results/|title=Finding the way|accessdate=2007-11-11|publisher=WWE}}</ref>

=====Hawkins and Ryder; La Familia (2007<U+2013>2009)=====
At [[Armageddon (2007)|Armageddon]], the duo dressed up like [[Edge (wrestler)|Edge]] and interfered in the [[World Heavyweight Championship (WWE)|World Heavyweight Championship]] match, replacing Edge at several points along the match to help him win the title and thus [[List of professional wrestling terms#T|turning]] [[Heel (professional wrestling)|heel]] for the first time in their WWE career.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wwe.com/shows/armageddon/history/2007/exclusives/majorrevelation|title=A Major revelation|date=2007-12-17|last=Dee|first=Louie|accessdate=2007-12-17|publisher=WWE}}</ref> On December 21, 2007, the Major Brothers were revealed as an acquaintance to Edge and his lover, ''SmackDown'' [[Professional wrestling authority figures#General managers 2|General Manager]] [[Vickie Guerrero]]. The Major Brothers were repackaged and renamed, as Brett Major's name was changed to "Zack Ryder" and Brian Major to "Curt Hawkins".<ref name="Three">{{cite web|url=http://www.wwe.com/shows/smackdown/archive/12212007/articles/threeforall| accessdate=2007-12-21|title=Three for All|last=Dee|first=Louie|publisher=WWE|date=2009-08-12}}</ref> They were now called [[Curt Hawkins and Zack Ryder]], occassionally referred as "The Rated-R Entourage" by commentators [[Michael Cole]] and [[John Layfield|John "Bradshaw" Layfield]]. . Occasionally teaming with their mentor Edge and/or their "[[La Familia (professional wrestling)|La Familia]]" associate Chavo Guerrero on ''SmackDown'' on several occasions. 

At [[The Great American Bash (2008)|The Great American Bash]] on July 20, 2008, Hawkins and Ryder won the [[WWE Tag Team Championship]] from [[John Morrison and The Miz]] in a [[Professional wrestling match types#Basic non-elimination matches|fatal four-way match]] which also featured [[Jesse and Festus]] and [[Dave Finlay|Finlay]] and [[Hornswoggle]] after Hawkins pinned Jesse.<ref name="WWE-Tag1">{{cite web|url=http://www.wwe.com/inside/titlehistory/wwetag/20080720|title=History Of The WWE Tag Team Championship - Curt Hawkins & Zack Ryder|date=2008-07-20|accessdate=2008-07-21|publisher=WWE}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wwe.com/shows/thegreatamericanbash/matches/7599484/results/|title=Out of the shadows, into the golden light|date= 2008-07-20|last=Passero|first=Mitch|accessdate=2008-07-21|publisher=WWE}}</ref> Their victory meant that they were the youngest tag team champions in WWE history.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wwe.com/shows/smackdown/archive/08082008/articles/HawkinsandRyderyoungesttagchamps|title=Hawkins and Ryder: WWE's youngest Tag Team Champions|date=2008-08-07|accessdate=2008-08-08| publisher=WWE}}</ref> At [[Summerslam 2008|SummerSlam]], La Familia seemed to have ended when a returning Undertaker sent Edge to Hell and then refused to forgive Vickie - prompting all the members to abandon Vickie, who would later align with Big Show. On the September 26, 2008 airing of ''SmackDown'', Curt Hawkins and Zack Ryder lost the titles to [[Carlito (wrestler)|Carlito]] and [[Primo Col<U+00F3>n]] in their first televised title defense.<ref name=WV-tapings>{{cite web|first=Adam|last=Martin|title=Friday Night Smackdown Tapings - Columbus (Last show on CW)|url=http://www.wrestleview.com/news2008/1222057185.shtml|date=2008-09-22|accessdate=2008-09-22|publisher=WrestleView.com}}</ref> On December 5, 2008 edition of ''SmackDown'', they returned in a [[Professional wrestling match types#Gauntlet match|tag team gauntlet match]] against [[Jeff Hardy]] and [[Triple H]] where they were the first and only team eliminated.

On April 15, 2009, Ryder was drafted back to the ECW brand as part of the [[2009 WWE Draft#Supplemental Draft|2009 Supplemental Draft]], separating the team.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wwe.com/shows/raw/2009draft/2009supplementaldraftresults/|title=2009 WWE Supplemental Draft results|date=2009-04-15|accessdate=2009-04-15|publisher=[[World Wrestling Entertainment]]}}</ref>

====Singles career (2009-present)====
Following the draft, Hawkins would spend months on hiatus from television before voluntarily leaving the main roster for training by going to [[Florida Championship Wrestling|FCW]]<ref>http://www.wrestlingepicenter.com/01020309articles//252172601.shtml</ref><ref>http://www.themayhem.com/showthread.php?t=11987</ref><ref>http://www.gerweck.net/news/1250198506.shtml</ref><ref>http://www.wrestleview.com/news2009/1250144464.php</ref>, losing to [[David Otunga|Dawson Alexander]] when he debuted on the show.<ref name="hawkfcw">{{cite web|url=http://www.411mania.com/wrestling/news/112691/FCW-Results-8.06.09:-Tampa,-FL.htm|title=FCW Results 8.06.09: Tampa, FL |last=Csonka|first=Larry|date=2009-08-07|publisher=411mania.com|accessdate=2009-09-05}}</ref> In the following weeks, Hawkins would go on to win an 8-man battle royal to become the number one contender for [[Paul Lloyd, Jr.|Justin Angel]]'s [[FCW Florida Heavyweight Championship]] but subsequently went on to lose the title match.<ref>http://www.pwinsider.com/article/42801/florida-championship-wrestling-tv-spoiler-results-from-tampa-florida-tommy-dreamer-vs-eric-escobar-and-more.html?p=1</ref> He would later join a stable called "The Dude Busters" alongside [[Kris Pavone|Caylen Croft]] and [[Trent Barreta]].<ref>http://www.pwinsider.com/article/41398/florida-championship-wrestling-in-punta-gorda-fl-results.html?p=1</ref> In late November, Hawkins and Croft won the [[Florida Championship Wrestling#FCW Florida Tag Team Championship|FCW Florida Tag Team Championship]]<ref name="fcwtag">{{cite web|url=http://www.411mania.com/wrestling/news/122559/FCW-TV-Taping-Results-%5BSpoilers%5D.htm|title=FCW TV Taping Results [Spoilers]|last=Ashis|date=20 November 2009|publisher=411mania.com|accessdate=27 November 2009}}</ref> although The Dude Busters would be defending the titles under the "Freebird Rule".<ref>http://www.pwinsider.com/article/43134/florida-championship-wrestling-tv-taping-results-irwin-r-shyster-appears-kaval-low-ki-back-in-action-and-more.html?p=1</ref><ref>http://www.lordsofpain.net/news/wwe/5075.html</ref><ref>http://www.wrestlingrevealed.com/news/update-on-curt-hawkins/</ref> On January 14, 2010 at an FCW television taping, The Dude Busters lost the FCW Florida Tag Team Championship to The Fortunate Sons ([[Brett DiBiase]] and [[Joe Hennig]]).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wrestleview.com/news2009/1263579090.php?style=dark|title=FCW crowns new tag champions|date=2010-01-15|last=Gerweck|first=Steve|accessdate=2010-01-16|publisher=WrestleView}}</ref>

Hawkins returned to the SmackDown roster in May 2010, forming a tag team with [[Lance Hoyt|Vance Archer]]. The team made its television debut defeating two local competitors on the May 13 edition of ''[[WWE Superstars]]''. After the match, Hawkins stated that he and Archer had been given a 30-day contract to "make an impact."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wwe.com/shows/wwesuperstars/results/14427924/|title=How to make an impact|publisher=[[World Wrestling Entertainment]]|first=Ryan|last=Murphy|date=May 13, 2010|accessdateMay 13, 2010}}</ref>

